{
  "chapter": {
    "id": "dra:first-chronicles.3",
    "translationId": "dra",
    "bookSlug": "first-chronicles",
    "chapterNumber": 3,
    "referenceLabel": "1 Chronicles 3",
    "summary": "Source text for 1 Chronicles 3 in Douay-Rheims Bible (Challoner)."
  },
  "verses": [
    {
      "id": "dra:first-chronicles.3.1",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "first-chronicles",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 1,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Chronicles 3:1",
      "text": "Now these were the sons of David that were born to him in Hebron: the firstborn Amnon of Achinoam the Jezrahelitess, the second Daniel of Abigail the Carmelitess.",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:first-chronicles.3.2",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "first-chronicles",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 2,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Chronicles 3:2",
      "text": "The third Absalom the son of Maacha the daughter of Tolmai king of Gessur, the fourth Adonias the son of Aggith,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:first-chronicles.3.3",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "first-chronicles",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 3,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Chronicles 3:3",
      "text": "The fifth Saphatias of Abital, the sixth Jethrahem of Egla his wife.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:first-chronicles.3.4",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "first-chronicles",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 4,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Chronicles 3:4",
      "text": "So six sons were born to him in Hebron, where he reigned seven years and six months. And in Jerusalem he reigned three and thirty years.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:first-chronicles.3.5",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "first-chronicles",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 5,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Chronicles 3:5",
      "text": "And these sons were born to him in Jerusalem: Simmaa, and Sobab, and Nathan, and Solomon, four of Bethsabee the daughter of Ammiel.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:first-chronicles.3.6",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "first-chronicles",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 6,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Chronicles 3:6",
      "text": "Jebaar also and Elisama,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:first-chronicles.3.7",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "first-chronicles",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 7,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Chronicles 3:7",
      "text": "And Eliphaleth, and Noge, and Nepheg, and Japhia,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:first-chronicles.3.8",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "first-chronicles",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 8,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Chronicles 3:8",
      "text": "And Elisama, and Eliada, and Elipheleth, nine:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:first-chronicles.3.9",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "first-chronicles",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 9,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Chronicles 3:9",
      "text": "All these the sons of David, beside the sons of the concubines: and they had a sister Thamar.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:first-chronicles.3.10",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "first-chronicles",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 10,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Chronicles 3:10",
      "text": "And Solomon's son was Roboam: whose son Abia begot Asa. And his son was Josaphat,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:first-chronicles.3.11",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "first-chronicles",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 11,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Chronicles 3:11",
      "text": "The father of Joram: and Joram begot Ochozias, of whom was born Joas:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:first-chronicles.3.12",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "first-chronicles",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 12,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Chronicles 3:12",
      "text": "And his son Amasias begot Azarias. And Joathan the son of Azarias",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:first-chronicles.3.13",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "first-chronicles",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 13,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Chronicles 3:13",
      "text": "Begot Achaz, the father of Ezechias, of whom was born Manasses.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:first-chronicles.3.14",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "first-chronicles",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 14,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Chronicles 3:14",
      "text": "And Manasses begot Amon the father of Josias.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:first-chronicles.3.15",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "first-chronicles",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 15,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Chronicles 3:15",
      "text": "And the sons of Josias were, the firstborn Johanan, the second Joakim, the third Sedecias, the fourth Sellum.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:first-chronicles.3.16",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "first-chronicles",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 16,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Chronicles 3:16",
      "text": "Of Joakim was born Jechonias, and Sedecias.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:first-chronicles.3.17",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "first-chronicles",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 17,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Chronicles 3:17",
      "text": "The sons of Jechonias were Asir, Salathiel,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:first-chronicles.3.18",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "first-chronicles",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 18,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Chronicles 3:18",
      "text": "Melchiram, Phadaia, Senneser and Jecemia, Sama, and Nadabia.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:first-chronicles.3.19",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "first-chronicles",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 19,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Chronicles 3:19",
      "text": "Of Phadaia were born Zorobabel and Semei. Zorobabel begot Mosollam, Hananias, and Salomith their sister:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:first-chronicles.3.20",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "first-chronicles",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 20,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Chronicles 3:20",
      "text": "Hasaba also, and Ohol, and Barachias, and Hasadias, Josabhesed, five.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:first-chronicles.3.21",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "first-chronicles",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 21,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Chronicles 3:21",
      "text": "And the son of Hananias was Phaltias the father of Jeseias, whose son was Raphaia. And his son was Arnan, of whom was born Obdia, whose son was Sechenias.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:first-chronicles.3.22",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "first-chronicles",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 22,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Chronicles 3:22",
      "text": "The son of Sechenias was Semeia, whose sons were Hattus, and Jegaal, and Baria, and Naaria, and Saphat, six in number.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:first-chronicles.3.23",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "first-chronicles",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 23,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Chronicles 3:23",
      "text": "The sons of Naaria, Elioenai, and Ezechias, and Ezricam, three.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:first-chronicles.3.24",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "first-chronicles",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 24,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Chronicles 3:24",
      "text": "The sons of Elioenai, Oduia, and Eliasub, and Pheleia, and Accub, and Johanan, and Dalaia, and Anani, seven.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    }
  ]
}
